).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">What training, qualifications and experience DO the “assessed individuals” actually possess?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The corner stone of competence MUST be the ability to actually DO the work – currently it is not.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It has been stated that t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he electrical industry is complicated – the reality is that it is as complicated as the vested interests have made it for their own commercial advantage.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">1. The Basic principle of a trained, qualified and experienced individual working, often unsupervised,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> in the homes of the public is simple and straightforward. The complications arise due to the way various bodies have set out to systematically mislead both the public and Parliament with regards fulfilling public expectation. The public are fully aware of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> what training, qualifications, experience and abilities an “electrician” should possess – so the “industry” has been more than willing to present their members as “electricians” without actually fulfilling said public expectation. This is a far, far more </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">profitable approach ....</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2. In my considerable experience, the probability of domestic electrical work complying with the Wiring Regulations (BS7671 – the British Standard against which electrical installation work is certified as compliant) is primarily d</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">etermined by whether or not the INSTALLER that actually carried out the work is a trained, qual</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ified and experienced electrician. The issue of Competent Person Scheme membership appears to be a near irrelevance. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">How can an individual be competent if th</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ey are unable to actually carry out the work the British Standard that they are certifying against? </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> The corner stone of competence MUST be the ability to actually DO the work – currently it is not.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4. The Part P Schemes will not admit that their membershi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">p includes “five day wonders” – so where HAVE they all gone - as by my estimate over 80% of new Registrants to electrical Competent Persons Schemes since 2005 have been the same “five day wonders”</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">What training, qualifications and experience DO the “a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ssessed individuals” actually possess?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">6. It is unfeasible that an inexperienced individual can be competent after only having undertaken a few days training.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">7. Quite how work carried out by an untrained, inexperienced operative under the “supervision” o</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">f a totally absent “Qualified Supervisor” is absurd. The Electrical Installation Certificates</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">(EIC`s)  ac</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">co</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">mpanying much of this work are totally inaccurate (bordering on fraudulent) or not even appropriate, quite often including details of safety</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> devices that do not exist yet with “test results” </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">obtained </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">for them!</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">8. In reality it takes an electrician to know if electrical work is compliant with BS7671 (not merely an “inspector”) – yet it is the non-competent householder who is held responsible fo</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">r meeting the Building Regulations and raising any complaint.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">9. The issue of complaints deteriorates into farce. The Part P “industry” assesses it`s own members (but does not actually certify them as “competent”) AND runs it`s own complaints procedures. T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">here is NO independence or impartiality at all. The concept that UKAS Accreditation will address such issues has already proven to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">be </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">nonsense.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">10. UKAS merely accredits an entity against the policies and procedures that they are presented with – yet these</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> same policies and procedures can be, and are, written by the Part P industry themselves.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">11. It must be noted that with regards monitoring of the Scheme Operators there appears only to be a requirement for the Schemes to document their CAPACITY to both me</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">et their Terms of Authorisation and manage any conflicts of interest. No mention is made of monitoring whether (or not) the said Terms of Authorisation are ACTUALLY met or if conflicts of interest are ACTUALLY avoided or dealt with effectively.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">12. Surely </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS cannot both accredit AND monitor the same organisation?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">13. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The curren</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, abysmal, state of the industry is due</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> in no small part</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> to the belief by the Schemes that the truth will never come out as any wide</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">scale misconduct or malpractice can be dismisse</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d as a series of “one-offs”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="fon